00:31:52.080 --> 00:31:54.896
AUDIENCE: I'm curious kind of
the difference between the--

00:31:54.896 --> 00:31:57.270
I've heard it talked about as
the subconscious background

00:31:57.270 --> 00:32:00.360
processing thinking
versus elastic thinking.

00:32:00.360 --> 00:32:03.602
Like, you read a riddle
right before you go to bed.

00:32:03.602 --> 00:32:06.060
And then you wake up and you
either dream about the answer,

00:32:06.060 --> 00:32:08.850
or just the answer hit
you out of nowhere.

00:32:08.850 --> 00:32:12.387
Or is this the same thing
as the shower epiphany

00:32:12.387 --> 00:32:13.470
that a lot of people have?

00:32:13.470 --> 00:32:14.510
LEONARD MLODINOW: Right.

00:32:14.510 --> 00:32:17.850
They're all related--
when you have a problem

00:32:17.850 --> 00:32:21.270
that you set up
analytically in your head.

00:32:21.270 --> 00:32:26.220
But the answer is not the
product of an algorithm.

00:32:26.220 --> 00:32:28.210
The answer is,
let's say, changing

00:32:28.210 --> 00:32:30.150
the way you solved a
problem, for instance--

00:32:30.150 --> 00:32:34.560
changing your assumptions,
or changing the paradigm.

00:32:37.270 --> 00:32:39.066
It's more like you
guys are started

00:32:39.066 --> 00:32:40.440
to use these neural
nets, which I

00:32:40.440 --> 00:32:45.086
think is the key to success
in computer science.

00:32:45.086 --> 00:32:49.200
And I wrote a paper
in the '80s about it.

00:32:49.200 --> 00:32:51.836
So that's elastic thinking.

00:32:51.836 --> 00:32:53.460
The neural nets--
with the neural nets,

00:32:53.460 --> 00:32:55.080
though, you don't know how
it got to the answer, right?

00:32:55.080 --> 00:32:56.940
You set it up so
that the computer is

00:32:56.940 --> 00:32:59.770
doing this crazy stuff
and it's learning.

00:32:59.770 --> 00:33:01.880
And at the end,
you don't know what

00:33:01.880 --> 00:33:04.357
algorithm it used in its
brain to get the answer.

00:33:04.357 --> 00:33:05.940
And that's the same
thing with humans.

00:33:05.940 --> 00:33:08.880
And so when you get these
ideas, it's from the bottom up.

00:33:08.880 --> 00:33:12.344
It's your neural nets in your
brain doing some calculation,

00:33:12.344 --> 00:33:13.260
giving you the answer.

00:33:13.260 --> 00:33:15.476
It's not some algorithm
saying, do this then do this

00:33:15.476 --> 00:33:16.860
and then do that.

00:33:16.860 --> 00:33:21.302
So yes, that's really the
big difference, is that--

00:33:21.302 --> 00:33:23.760
or one of the big differences--
is that analytical thinking

00:33:23.760 --> 00:33:26.640
tends to be top down,
and elastic thinking

00:33:26.640 --> 00:33:29.763
tends to be bottom
up calculation.

